description:
ITV Tour de France 2016 Stage 10 PDTV x264-NX

12th July 2016 ITV4
14:00 to 16:30 Stage 10

Gary Imlach and Chris Boardman present live coverage of stage 10. This classic stage for the long-distance escape artists starts with 24km of relentless climbing on the category 1 Port d'Envalira. 170km of sinuous roads follow, before the crux of the stage - the category 3 ramp of the Cote de Saint Ferreol. Just 7km before the finish line, it has the potential to fragment the front end of the race. Commentary by Ned Boulting and David Millar with Daniel Friebe reporting from the roadside.
